        <div class="verdict">✓ Updated April 2026</div>

        <p>Autodesk Build and Fieldwire both target the field side of construction management — drawings, tasks, issues, and inspections. The difference is depth and scope. Autodesk Build is part of the Autodesk Construction Cloud ecosystem, connecting field execution to design tools (Revit, AutoCAD, Navisworks) and enterprise project management. Fieldwire is a focused, field-first platform that does a smaller set of things exceptionally well.</p>

        <p>The comparison often comes down to one question: how connected is your field team to your design and engineering process?</p>

